{"word":"G1704 - ἐμπεριπατέω - emperipatéō - em-per-ee-pat-eh'-o - Walk in","slug":"G1704","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<strong>Original: </strong><span class=\"hebrewOrGreek\">ἐμπεριπατέω</span>"},{"paragraph":"<strong>Transliteration: </strong>emperipatéō"},{"paragraph":"<strong>Phonetic: </strong>em-per-ee-pat-eh'-o"},{"paragraph":"<strong>Short Definition: </strong>Walk in"},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<b>&#x03B5;&#x0313;&#x03BC;&#x03C0;&#x03B5;&#x03C1;&#x03B9;&#x03C0;&#x03B1;&#x03C4;&#x03B5;&#x0301;&#x03C9; - emperipateo&#x0304;</b> - <i>em-per-ee-pat-eh'-o</i><p/>From <a href=\"#/G1722\">G1722</a> and <a href=\"#/G4043\">G4043</a>; to <i>perambulate on</i> a place, that is, (figuratively) to <i>be occupied among</i> persons: - walk in."},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<strong>Cognate:</strong> <a href=\"#/G2662\">G2662</a>, <a href=\"#/G3961\">G3961</a>, <a href=\"#/G4043\">G4043</a>"}]}